transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, my name is Nicholas Mendoza and I just wanted to change the...

Speaker 1: I wanted to see, first of all, if it's like a recurring thing,

Speaker 2: you guys like send the same thing over and over each month or do I have to do that manually?

Speaker 1: Let me pull up your profile. Nicholas, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: Yeah, 7-28-1981.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much. I see you're a VIP status customer

Speaker 2: and it looks like the doctor put you on automatic refills every two months.

Speaker 1: How's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It's fine. Yeah, it's fine. It works just fine.

Speaker 1: I was using that Bluetooth stuff and it was giving me like a really bad headache.

Speaker 2: This one doesn't give me a headache, so I'm cool with that.

Speaker 1: Okay, good. Yeah, and with your VIP status, you don't have to have your refills every two months.

Speaker 2: You know, you can change that to your liking in monthly increments every three months, every four months.

Speaker 1: Some people just like to go ahead and put a six-month hold on it.

Speaker 2: It keeps your prescription active and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: Yeah, can you help me out with that because I tried to do that on you guys' web page.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you got to call.

Speaker 1: Okay, I got it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you got to get a call. Yeah.

Speaker 1: Got it.

Speaker 2: And I'm going to pause you until July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And also just a reminder, whenever you call in and if you do a refill on your computer like online,

Speaker 1: it will automatically put you back to every two months.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And then when you call in or if you call in to get a refill, sometimes people don't look that you're on a six-month hold.

Speaker 2: So just remind them, hey, I want a refill, but pause it again for six months.

Speaker 1: Okay, got it, got it.

Speaker 2: Okay, so just call back if like if I want another refill more soon, then I just call you guys back.

Speaker 1: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 2: Okay, cool, cool. I'll do that.

Speaker 1: And you're going to go ahead and set that six-month thing up for me.

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, you're paused until July 31st.

Speaker 1: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 2: All right, thanks a lot for your help.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, not a problem.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
